    "body": "By the way, I've been thinking about this and i think we might want to add a \"default\" returnvalue to calls. this is a more general mechanism for dealing with contracts which return less data than expected, so we do not have to add a builtin for every ERC20 (or, could be other standards) function implementation which is buggy. something like\r\n```vyper\r\nExternalContract(msg.sender).some_function(<args>, default=False)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe compiler can issue code to fill the return buffer with the `default` value if `returndatasize` is empty.",
